  number={},
  pages={327-328},
  abstract={Taking the advantages of reciprocity and randomness of wireless fading channels, key generation via physical layer is attracting more attention. It becomes a remarkable solution for wireless communication in recent years. However, the feasibility under long-range and low data rate scenarios of narrow band low power wide area network (LPWAN) lacks proper studies. In this poster, we introduce a novel modeling method for Long Range Wide Area Network (LoRaWAN) key generation. The approach combines several signal processing techniques and using measured real-time Received Signal Strength Indicator (RSSI) to improve the applicability of key generation as well as increasing key generation rate (KGR) significantly.},
